other_tests.findings: In the right lower quadrant, there is subtle stranding, hyperemia, and enlargement of the appendix measuring up to 10 mm. No evidence of perforation or abscess formation. Several subcentimeter hypodensities in the liver, potential cysts or hemangiomas. Layering small hyperdense stones in the gallbladder, no cholecystitis. No free air or free fluid in the abdomen.
